  "body": "**Description**: We recently added dynamic_metadata action (issue #11593) that gets descriptor information from the metadata. As currently built the dynamic_metadata action looks for information in the dynamic metadata and if isn\u2019t there it stops and does not build the descriptor. We now realize there may be instances where the information isn\u2019t there because of the failure of another filter, it never existed or some other edge case. So instead of letting the descriptor fail, we would like to include an optional default string value for instances where the information is not in the dynamic metadata.\u00a0\r\n\r\nThe updated schema would look like:\r\n\u2028\r\n```yaml\r\n- dynamic_metadata:\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 descriptor_key: \u201c\u2026\u201d\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 default: \u201c\u2026\u201d\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 metadata_key:\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 key: \u201c\u2026\u201d\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 path:\r\n\u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0 - key: \u201c\u2026\u201d\r\n```",
